  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to evaluate the efficacy and feasibility of active video gaming
      with regard to the promotion of physical activity and motor learning in children with
      cancer. Experienced fatigue, body mass index and the development of metabolic risk factors
      during treatment are also examined.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
